          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/15/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Follow-up SLE, lupus nephritis, CKD.
HPI: 42yo Hispanic female with SLE and class IV lupus nephritis. Recovered from flare in Nov -- completed pulse methylprednisolone. Currently on maintenance mycophenolate 2g/day + HCQ + prednisone 5mg. Reports improved energy, no joint pain, no rash. Occasional Raynaud episodes in cold weather.
Labs: Cr 1.4 (stable), eGFR 48, proteinuria improving (850 from 1200). Complements low but stable. dsDNA elevated but trending down.
PE: Afebrile. No malar rash. Joints -- no synovitis. Lungs clear. CV RRR. No edema.
Assessment:
# Lupus nephritis (M32.14): Improving on mycophenolate. Continue current dose.
# CKD 3a (N18.31): Cr stable 1.4. Continue losartan for nephroprotection.
# Anemia (D50.9): Hgb 10.8, ferritin 12. Start ferrous sulfate 325mg BID. Recheck in 6 weeks.
# HTN (I10): BP 128/78 at goal. Continue losartan + amlodipine.
# Vit D deficiency: Level 18. Continue ergocalciferol 50K weekly.
Plan: Continue immunosuppression. Add iron. Nephrology follow-up in 6 weeks. Ophthalmology due for HCQ screening (annual). Labs 6 weeks.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>11/15/2025</td><td>Gretchen Lockard, MD</td><td>Acute Visit</td><td>CC: Joint pain, facial rash, fever x 3 days.
HPI: 42yo with SLE presents with classic flare symptoms. Butterfly rash returned, polyarthritis affecting hands/wrists/knees. Low-grade fever 100.4. Dark urine noted.
PE: Malar rash present. Synovitis bilateral MCPs, wrists, knees. Oral ulcers x2 on buccal mucosa. Lungs clear. No edema.
Labs: Cr up from 1.2 to 1.8, proteinuria 1200 mg/g, C3/C4 both low, dsDNA 120 IU/mL, WBC 2.9.
Assessment: SLE flare with nephritis activity.
Plan: Pulse methylprednisolone 1g IV x 3 days then taper. Increase mycophenolate to 3g/day temporarily. Urgent nephrology consult. Hold losartan temporarily if Cr continues rising. Weekly labs.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>08/20/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT
42yo female with SLE.
Preventive:
- Cervical cancer: Pap + HPV co-test 2023. Next due 2028.
- Breast cancer: Mammogram baseline age 40 done 2023. Due 2025 -- ordered.
- Colorectal: Not yet due (age 42). Will start at 45.
- Depression: PHQ-9 = 12 (moderate). Continue escitalopram. Counseling referral offered.
- Bone density: DEXA ordered -- chronic steroid use.
- Ophthalmology: HCQ screening annual -- due now.
- Vaccines: Flu given. PCV20 given (immunocompromised).
Advance Directive: Discussed, patient will complete.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
